  "grammarNote": {
    "title": "The Conditional: Would, Could",
    "explanation": "Le truc servirait bien. — the thing WOULD work well. Notice the ending -rait: it means something is possible but not certain.\n\nCompare: sert (it serves — present) vs. servirait (it would serve — conditional). The -rait ending adds doubt.\n\nRe-read and find every -rait or -rais ending. What is uncertain or hoped for?"
